    "Our theorems apply to the interaction kernels of the bounded interaction and the Biot-Savart interaction as in [33] for the Fokker-Planck equation.",
    "But due to the challenges from the Lévy score, we have not yet prove for the Column interaction as the diffusion process in [33].",
    "• The generalized score function trained in Algorithm 3.1 contains the contributions of drift, interaction, diffusion and jump; thus, the transport for the N deterministic particles are independent of each other, while [29] still evolves the N interactive particles with the mean-field interaction.",
    "• Even though our numerical algorithm to train the score is sequential in time as in [4], the approach in [25] of the self-consistent velocity matching by learning from the whole simulated trajectories until a terminal time is applicable to the Lévy-Fokker-Planck equation here, because the same fixed-point formulation works with the new defined Lévy score function in our work.The structure of this paper is as follows: Section 2 shows how to define the This manuscript is for review purposes only.generalized score function (the diffusion score and the Lévy score) and establish the probability flow equivalence.",
